latestIgtvVideos.title: DoctorSpeak: How do you choose a floor cleaner?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
☘How do you choose a floor cleaner that is tough on the germs + grim and safe for  your family and pets. Here are some useful tips:

⚠️ Avoid cleaners that are heavily loaded with potent chemicals like: 

🧪 Benzalkonium Chloride Solution

🧪 2-Butoxyethanol

🧪 Phthalates
 
🧪 Tetra Sodium EDTA.
 
🧼 These are known to have several long term health effects ranging from respiratory issues, skin allergies, hormone imbalances and some have even been linked to cancer causing toxins.

☘ Opt for our plant-based floor cleaner instead. 0% nasties and 100% clean.

latestIgtvVideos.title: DoctorSpeak: How do you choose a hand wash?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
☘️You’re probably washing your hands a dozen times a day. People with sensitive skin usually suffer the most. We have a few tips for you that will help you choose a better hand wash for daily use:

⚠️ Always check that your hand wash is free of these chemicals:

🧪 Parabens, avoid hand wash containing ingredients ending in – Paraben. They are associated with endocrine disruption, cancer, and developmental toxicity. They are also toxic to the environment.

🧪 Triclosan is a substance used as an antibacterial agent in hand washes. This nasty got banned by the FDA in 2016.  Risks are that it can accumulate over time in the body and cause hormonal imbalances and organ system toxicity.

🧪 Synthetic dyes - don’t be fooled by the lilac and bright pink shades of your hand wash. Those are artificially colours with a potential to cause serious damage to your skin and in some cases even linked to cancer causing heavy metals.

✅ Things you should do:

☘️ Go plant-based with a handwash that is free from harsh chemicals and synthetic dyes.

☘️ Make sure that your hand wash is suited for your skin type. The advantage of using plant based is that it’s highly adaptable to most skin types.

☘ Opt for our plant-based hand wash instead. 0% nasties and 100% clean.

latestIgtvVideos.title: DoctorSpeak: What are the golden rules of handwashing?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
✨ Golden rules you should follow every day to wash your hands the right way while ensuring no skin damage:

✅ Timing is really important, knowing when it’s necessary to give your hands a quick wash. One should definitely practice hand washing before, during and after preparing food. After handling pets. After cleaning. 

✅ Follow the right technique. Do thumb rotations on your palm with the lather, use the interlaced washing technique to get between your fingers.

✅ Make sure to include your wrists while washing your hands. Follow the 20-30 seconds rule.

✅  Use a plant-based hand wash, which is free of Parabens and Triclosan, these are extremely harmful for your skin and not recommended for children.
